Durable Functions - a long-running serverless workflow

Durable Functions is an extension of Azure Functions that enables you to perform long-lasting, stateful operations in Azure

Durable Functions is an extension of Azure Functions. Whereas Azure Functions operate in a stateless environment, Durable Functions can retain state between function calls.

Durable Functions scales as needed.

orchestration function

You can use three durable function types: Client, Orchestrator, and Activity.

You create a durable timer by calling the createTimer() method of the DurableOrchestrationContext

You should always use currentUtcDateTime to obtain the current date and time, instead of Date.now or Date.UTC.


